From 630ba80167c8c9d39e8d777fe74fc7cd0556dd48 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <quic_hbijlani@quicinc.com>
Date: Fri, 28 Mar 2025 18:24:18 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] wifi: ath12k: Use ath12k_dp_peer in per packet Tx & Rx
 path

As part of peer modularization in Unified Driver Framework, station view
for the data path is shown below:

ath12k_dp_peer
       |
       |-> ath12k_dp_link_peer
       |
       |-> ath12k_dp_link_peer
       |
       |-> ath12k_dp_link_peer

This ath12k_dp_peer contains the fields used in the per pkt Tx Rx paths
applicable across all the links and maintains an array of
ath12k_dp_link_peer. Per pkt Tx and Rx path operates on ath12k_dp_peer.

ath12k_dp_link_peer contains the fields specific to a link and these are
mostly for telemetry and monitor usage.

This patch is to move all the link agnostic fields from ath12k_dp_link_peer
to ath12k_dp_peer and make changes in the APIs wherever required.

Also make changes to fetch ath12k_dp_peer in per packet Tx and Rx paths
using peer_id instead of ath12k_dp_link_peer.

Signed-off-by: Harsh Kumar Bijlani <quic_hbijlani@quicinc.com>
